column3: Population by country/region of birth, Queensland, 1861 to 2006
Australia
Queensland
no.

�  Shown as nil      . .  Nil, or not published and included elsewhere. A country might not always be listed separately and may be included in Other Europe, Other Asia etc for certain years. Sometimes an area may be represented but wasn't a separate country at time of census, e.g. Pakistan, and areas that were often regarded as part of Syria (Greater Syria) before WWII.
nec  not elsewhere counted      nei  not elsewhere included      nfd  not further defined
To 1991, persons counted in Queensland at census time; from 1996, place of usual residence.
a  Other colonies/states - for 1868, 1971 and 1876, not disaggregated (except for Tasmania in 1868), and includes New Zealand, as part of Australasia; for 1971 and from 1981, not disaggregated.

b  Total Australia - for 1868, 1871 and 1876, includes New Zealand (as part of Australasia); for 1901, a total of 6,670 Aboriginal persons were counted separately and not included in the figures - would only include those in the settled districts; before 1971, censuses exclude full-blood Aboriginal people; for 1971, disaggregation by state and territory not published; before 1981, includes not stated; for 1986 and 1991, includes persons born at sea; for 1996, 2001 and 2006, count basis was 2,640,567, 2,786,286 and 2,982,381 respectively.
c  For 1996, Kiribati (97) and Tuvalu (15); for 2001, Kiribati (117) and Tuvalu (39); for 2006, Kiribati (121) and Tuvalu (70).
d  New Zealand - for 1868, 1871 and 1876, included with Australia (as part of Australasia).
e  Papua New Guinea - before 1947, refers to the separate territories of Papua and New Guinea; for 1971, Australian External Territories, which would mainly (nearly all?) be Papua New Guinea.
f  Samoa - for 1996, 2001 and 2006, includes American Samoa (25, 56 and 76 respectively).

g  Other Oceania / Pacific Islands / Polynesia - for 1868, 1871, 1876, 1881, 1886 and 1891, Polynesian, and includes 7, 81, 170, 396, 964 and 781 females respectively; for 1881, 1886, 1891 and 1901, includes 48, 101, 95 and 49 born of white parents respectively; for 1901, South Sea Is. so described (8,809) and Other Polynesian British Possessions (6), including 431 females; for 1911, British Polynesia undefined (1), Fanning Is (1), Gilbert Is (1), Raratonga (1), Santa Cruz Is (3), Savage Is (4), Caroline Is (2), Low Archipelago (5), Polynesia undefined (153), Society Is (1) and South Sea Is. so described (490); for 1921, Other British Islands (257), Society Islands (6) and Other Polynesian Islands (6); for 1933, Other British Possessions in Polynesia (122), Society Islands (5) and Other Polynesian Islands (170); for 1947, Other British Possessions in Polynesia (35), Society Islands (9) and Other Polynesian Islands (9); from 1954, not disaggregated, except sometimes for Other Commonwealth and Other; for 2001, Polynesia nec (15); for 2001, Marshall Islands (11), Micronesia nfd (16).

h  Totals for Oceania, Europe, Asia, North America, South America and Africa - for 1991, figures would be lower than actual as countries in all continents would be included in the published figure of 'Other' (34,959), which also includes inadequately described, at sea and not elsewhere classified.
i  England - for 1976, 1981 and 1986, England including UK undefined.
j  Ireland - from 1947, Ireland undefined; for 1976 to 2001, Eire / Republic of Ireland including Ireland undefined, which may be mainly Ireland undefined.
k  Northern Ireland existed from 1921 but separate figures available only from 1947.
l  Republic of Ireland existed from 1921 but separate figures available only from 1947.
m  United Kingdom (England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland) - for 1991, disaggregation not published.
n  United Kingdom, not stated - for 1886 and 1891, British subjects, birthplace not stated; for 1996, 2001 and 2006, United Kingdom nfd.
o  Austria - for 1901 and 1911, Austria-Hungary.
p  Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia, and Slovenia - before 1996, part of Yugoslavia; Montenegro included as part of Yugoslavia before 2006.
q  Czech Republic and Slovakia - before 1996, part of Czechoslovakia.
r  Czechoslovakia - became Czech Republic and Slovakia in 1993; for 1996, Former Czechoslovakia nfd.
s  Germany - for 1954 to 1986, East and West Germany.
t  Hungary - to 1911, included as part of Austria-Hungary.
u  Norway - to 1901, included under Sweden & Norway.
v  Russia - for 1954 to 1991, Other USSR / USSR nei but not including Ukraine; for 1966, USSR nei, but including Ukraine; for 1996 and 2001, Russian Federation.
w  Serbia - from 1921 to 2001, recorded as part of Yugoslavia.
x  Sweden - to 1901, included under Sweden & Norway.
y  Ukraine - for 1966, included with Russia (USSR)
z  Yugoslavia - for 1996 and 2001, Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, including Former Yugoslavia nfd.

aa  Other Europe - not disaggregated by country, except for 1911, which consisted of Azores (1), Crete (2) and Europe undefined (6); for 1996, Eastern Europe nfd (138); for 2001, Eastern Europe nfd (904) and South Eastern Europe nfd (353); for 2006, Eastern Europe nfd (829), Faeroe Islands (12) and South Eastern Europe nfd (3,932).
ab  Cambodia - for 1971, included with Vietnam.

ac  China - For 1861, 1864, 1868, 1871, 1876, 1881, 1886, 1891, 1901, 1911, 1921 and 1933, includes 1, 0, 8, 1, 13, 29, 44, 41, 106, 80, 81 and 140 females respectively; for 1871 and 1876, includes Japan; for 1881, 1886, 1891 and 1901, includes 24, 28, 32 and 27 persons born of white parents respectively; more recent figures exclude Special Administrative Regions and Taiwan.

ad  India - for 1868, includes Other British Dominions; for 1881, 1886, 1891 and 1901, includes 315, 539, 552 and 445 persons born of white parents respectively; for 1901, 1911, 1921, 1933 and 1947, British India; for 1947, includes Ceylon (now Sri Lanka).

ae  Indonesia - for 1911, the areas that later made up Indonesia: Java (304), Amboina (1), Banda Is (2), Borneo (2), Celebes (4), Dutch East Indies undefined (4), Sumatra (4) and Timor (2); for 1921 and 1933, Java (including 1 from Timor in 1933), with other areas probably included in Other Countries in Asia; for 1947, Netherlands East Indies (154) and Timor (19).
af  Iran - for 1971, includes Iraq.
ag  Japan - for 1886, 1891 and 1901, includes 1, 0 and 2 persons respectively born of white parents; for 1901, 1911, 1921 and 1933, includes 144, 65, 43 and 26 females respectively.
ah  Korea - from 1971 to 1986, includes North Korea.
ai  Laos - for 1971, included with Vietnam.
aj  Lebanon - for 1947, included with Syria.

ak  Malaysia - for 1886, 1891 and 1901, Malay Peninsula and Archipelago (plus Straits Settlements, which include Singapore, for 1901), and 55, 79 and 31 females respectively; for 1911, 1921 and 1933, Straits Settlements and Federated Malay States; for 1947, Malaya nei and Straits Settlements.
al  Saudi Arabia - from 1971, see 'Other Asia' column and footnote.
am  Sri Lanka - for 1947, included with India.
an  Syria - before WWII, Syria often meant Greater Syria and included Lebanon, Israel, Palestine, Jordan and southern Turkey; for 1947, includes Lebanon.
ao  Vietnam - for 1971, includes Cambodia and Laos.

ap  Other Asia - not disaggregated by country, except for 1911 which consists of Asia Minor (5), Siberia (4) and Asia undefined (3), and also Aden (4); for 1971, includes 'Jordan, Kuwait, Oman, Saudi Arabia, Yemen' (68); for 1976, includes 'Muscat, Saudi Arabia' (89); for 1981, includes 'Bahrain, Jordan, Kuwait, Muscat and Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Yemen' (126); for 1986, other Southern Asia (Afghanistan, Bhutan, Nepal, Maldives) (139) and Other Western Asia (170); for 1996, Middle East nfd (19); for 2001, Maritime South East Asia nfd (45), Middle East nfd (11) and Southern Asia nfd (11); for 2006, Armenia (24), Azerbaijan (20), Bhutan (13), Georgia (11), Maritime South East Asia nfd (24), South-East Asia nfd (27) and Uzbekistan (39).
aq  Canada - to 1881, 'British America'; from 1886, Canada; for 1901, 1911, 1921, 1933 and 1947, includes Newfoundland which became part of Canada in 1949 (17, 22, 13, 10 and 8 respectively).
ar  El Salvador - to 1981, included in Other North America column.
as  United States of America - for 1947 and 1954, includes Hawaiian Islands / Hawaii which became part of the US in 1959 (4 in both years).

at  West Indies / Caribbean - for 1901, Barbados (5) and Jamaica (39), although other West Indies countries would be included in Other North America; for 1911, Antigua (5), Bahamas (1), Barbados (8), British West Indies undefined (6), Jamaica (40), St Lucia (4), St Vincent (5), Trinidad (5), St Thomas (2), San Domingo (1) and West Indies undefined (39); for 1921, Barbados (6), British West Indies nei (39), Jamaica (26), West Indies nei (11); for 1933, Barbados (6), British West Indies nei (15), Jamaica (20), West Indies nei (19); for 1947, Barbados (4), British West Indies nei (13), Jamaica (15) and West Indies nei (8); for 1954, British West Indies (41) and West Indies nei (11); for 1961 and 1966, West Indies Federation; for 1971, 1976, 1981 and 1986, Commonwealth Countries of the West Indies and Caribbean; for 1996, Bahamas (40), Barbados (141), Caribbean nfd (88), Grenada (27), Jamaica (191), Martinique (11), Netherlands Antilles (36) and Trinidad and Tobago (268); for 2001, Bahamas (43), Barbados (134), Caribbean nfd (79), Dominican Republic (14), Grenada (38), Jamaica (193), Martinique (14), Netherlands Antilles (35), Puerto Rico (10), St Vincent and the Grenadines (10) and Trinidad and Tobago (286); for 2006, Aruba (12), Bahamas (46), Barbados (147), Caribbean, nfd (74), Cayman Islands (11), Dominican Republic (22), Grenada (32), Haiti (14), Jamaica (232), Martinique (12), Netherlands Antilles (48), Puerto Rico (18), St Kitts and Nevis (10) and Trinidad and Tobago (317).

au  Other North America - to 1891, Other States in America, and includes those in South America; for 1901, Other American British Possessions (156) and Other American Countries (98), and may include some in South America; for 1921, 1933 and 1947, Other British Possessions in America and Other Countries in America, which may include some in South America; from 1954, not disaggregated by country; for 1971, Other Countries in North and South America (185) and Other Countries in Central America (95); for 1976, Other Commonwealth Countries in America (76) and America - Other Countries (572) and may include some in South America; for 1981, America nei, and may include some in South America; for 1996, Belize (11); for 2001, Belize (10), Central America nfd (12) and Northern America nfd (13); for 2006, Greenland (11) and Northern America nfd (23).

av  Other South America - for 1911, Falkland Is (5) and South America undefined (38); from 1954 to 1966, not disaggregated by country; for various years, some may be included in the Other North America column as Other American Countries etc (see relevant footnote); for 2001, South America nec (96); for 2006, South America nec (137).
aw  Total South America - for 1901, 1921 and 1933, the undisaggregated category Other American Countries has been put in the Other North America column but may include some South American countries.
ax  Congo - for 1996, Democratic Republic of Congo; for 2001, Democratic Republic of Congo (51) and Republic of Congo (32); for 2006, Democratic Republic of Congo (81) and Republic of Congo (85).
ay  Egypt - for 1966, United Arab Republic.
az  Kenya - for 1976, part of 'Kenya, Malawi, Rhodesia, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia' in Other Africa column/footnote.

ba  South Africa - for 1901, Cape of Good Hope (42), Natal (15), Transvaal (1) and South Africa undefined (127); for 1911, Cape of Good Hope (79), Natal (28), Orange Free State (3), Transvaal (36) and South Africa undefined (237).

bb  Zimbabwe - for 1971, part of 'Malawi, Rhodesia [Zimbabwe], Zambia' in Other Africa column/footnote; for 1976, part of 'Kenya, Malawi, Rhodesia, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia' in Other Africa column/footnote.

bc  Other Africa - not disaggregated by country, except for 1911, which includes St Helena (13), Cape Verde Is (7) and Madeira (5); for 1921, includes St Helena (8), Cape Verde Islands (4), Madeira (2) and Tripoli (1); for 1933 and 1947, includes St Helena (5 and 2 respectively); for 1971, 'Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda' (512), 'Malawi, Rhodesia, Zambia' (340), Other Commonwealth Countries in Africa (141) and Other Countries in Africa (421); for 1976, 'Kenya, Malawi, Rhodesia, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia' (1,052), Other Commonwealth Countries in Africa (103) and Africa - Other Countries (692); for 1981, includes 'Malawi, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia' (466); for 1986, includes 'Malawi, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia' (702); for 1996, Central and West Africa nfd (39) and Southern and East Africa nfd (123); for 2001, Central and West Africa nfd (43) and Southern and East Africa nfd (146); for 2006, Burundi (184), Central and West Africa nfd (41), Gabon (10), Gambia (27), Guinea (42), North Africa nfd (18), Rwanda (63) and Southern and East Africa nfd (114).
bd  Other - for 1864, includes Other British Dominions; for 1861, 1864 and 1868, Other Foreign Countries; for 1991, would include countries in all continents plus Oceania.

be  Born at sea - for 1881, 1886, 1891 and 1901, divided into 'British subjects' (540, 786, 807 and 619 respectively) and 'Foreign subjects' (92, 58, 25 and 15); for 1986 and 1991, included in Total Australia.
bf  Not stated - from 1933 to 1976, included in Total Australia?; for 1996 and 2001, includes inadequately described and not elsewhere classified.
bg  Proportions - 'Not stated' responses excluded from calculations.

Registrar-General's Office, Queensland censuses of 1861 to 1901; Australian Bureau of Statistics, Commonwealth censuses of 1911 to 1991, including 1901 in 1911 census; for 1996 and 2001, Multicultural Affairs Queensland, The People of Queensland, Statistics from the 2001 Census; for 2001 and 2006, The People of Queensland, Statistics from the 2006 Census; ABS, Australian Historical Population Statistics, 2008, cat. no. 3105.0.65.001, tables 9.3 and 9.7 - 9.22
